            <thetext>Browsers launched by using the &quot;*custom&quot; launcher in Selenium frequently fail to respond to the stop() command. This can lead to problems if a subsequent test wants to use the same browser: Firefox pops up a &quot;Firefox process already running but not responding&quot; alert box even if called with the &quot;-no-remote&quot; switch.

A (Bash|VB)script could be used to kill any remaining browser processes after each test run.</thetext>
